# Clerk Auth and Data Ownership

All authentication is handled by Clerk. Application code must ensure users can only access data that belongs to their Clerk user.

- Use Clerk as the source of truth for the current user identity.
- Scope every user-owned read, write, update, and delete by the authenticated Clerk user id.
- For deck data, filter by [src/db/schema.ts](mdc:src/db/schema.ts) `decksTable.clerkUserId`.
- For card data, authorize through the owning deck before reading or mutating cards.
- Do not trust client-provided user ids, deck ids, or card ids as proof of access.
- If an unauthenticated user tries to access a protected page, redirect them to the homepage (`/`) so they can use the modal sign-in/sign-up buttons. Do not redirect to a standalone sign-in page; this app does not have one.
- When adding new user-owned tables, include an ownership path back to the Clerk user and enforce it in all queries.
